1
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:45,520
Mr. Suzuki's body

2
00:01:46,479 --> 00:01:48,140
was found in the Songhua River

3
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:49,720
this morning.

4
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:51,720
Who did this?

5
00:01:53,440 --> 00:01:54,700
What exactly happened

6
00:01:55,440 --> 00:01:56,600
last night?

7
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:02,000
Last night,

8
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:04,760
it went like this.

9
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,800
Deputy Section Chief Chen and I took Mr. Suzuki...

10
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:15,040
Mr. Suzuki took Deputy Section Chief Chen and me

11
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:16,079
on an operation.

12
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:19,560
Suddenly, he received a signal.

13
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:22,000
He ordered Deputy Section Chief Chen and me

14
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:23,520
to take our men and proceed.

15
00:02:23,520 --> 00:02:25,800
He took a group of men

16
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,260
and acted independently.

17
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:34,360
We wanted to protect Mr. Suzuki,

18
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:35,240
but

19
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:38,200
we couldn't disobey orders.

20
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:42,079
Yes.

21
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:43,480
We didn't dare to disobey

22
00:02:43,480 --> 00:02:44,720
Mr. Suzuki's orders.

23
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:45,560
But

24
00:02:45,920 --> 00:02:47,980
we have arranged a citywide manhunt.

25
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:50,320
We also discovered

26
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:52,920
Mr. Suzuki's killer.

27
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:55,600
His methods were extremely cruel.

28
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:56,360
It seems like

29
00:02:58,360 --> 00:03:00,440
the person we've been looking for.

30
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:10,640
The deadline to find the killer is thirty days.

31
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,060
How many days are left?

32
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,000
Seven days.

33
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:20,320
Seven days.

34
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:33,800
Qian Yugui.

35
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:37,320
If you don't catch the murderer within seven days,

36
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:38,840
you'll be buried

37
00:03:39,880 --> 00:03:41,000
with Mr. Suzuki.

38
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:42,760
Yes.

39
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:48,960
It won't take seven days.

40
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:51,000
We have found some clues.

41
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:52,640
This murderer...

42
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:53,920
He's missing

43
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:55,720
his left pinky.

44
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:57,960
And he's from Fangzheng County, right?

45
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:59,640
Fangzheng County. Yes, Fangzheng County.

46
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:01,200
He has a record. He killed a Japanese before.

47
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:02,640
I personally went to

48
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:04,090
his place a few days ago.

49
00:04:20,079 --> 00:04:20,940
Section Chief.

50
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:22,120
Seven days

51
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:23,490
will pass in a flash.

52
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:28,180
How about this.

53
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:29,860
Find a death row inmate

54
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:31,770
to impersonate him.

55
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,120
That could work.

56
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,360
But don't find someone weak

57
00:04:36,520 --> 00:04:37,720
who can't even write.

58
00:04:38,440 --> 00:04:39,360
Absolutely.

59
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:40,720
Chief.

60
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:41,920
Over here.

61
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:42,920
Chief.

62
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:45,240
Your wife was at the cafe entrance

63
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:46,400
and got beaten up.

64
00:04:49,960 --> 00:04:51,420
How dare they beat my wife!

65
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:53,320
Forget the death row inmate.

66
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:54,120
We'll use him.

67
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:55,040
Let's go.

68
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:02,520
Did everyone see that?

69
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:03,640
This woman,

70
00:05:03,880 --> 00:05:04,920
she is Japanese.

71
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,000
We can't afford to offend her.

72
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,040
I know, I know.

73
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:08,180
What about my wife?

74
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:09,000
Are you crazy?

75
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:09,720
I will talk nicely.

76
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:11,250
If anyone dares to cross us,

77
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:12,520
they will end up like her.

78
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:13,720
You are unreasonable.

79
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,440
Bastard!

80
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:18,880
Honey, honey.

81
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:20,090
Excuse me, make way.

82
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,000
Honey, are you okay?

83
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,120
Hubby, you are here.

84
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:23,000
What happened?

85
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:24,080
Are you okay?

86
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:26,280
She...

87
00:05:26,760 --> 00:05:28,600
Look, he hit me. Look.

88
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:29,920
I went shopping today,

89
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:31,180
and saw a dress I liked.

90
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:32,400
He asked for 200 yuan.

91
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:34,320
I asked for a discount, to sell it for 80.

92
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:35,120
Then he said,

93
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:36,240
'If you don't buy it, get lost.'

94
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:37,440
I just muttered a bit.

95
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:38,280
Then,

96
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:41,240
he just came up and slapped me

97
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:42,440
right here.

98
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:43,840
Look how bad he hit me.

99
00:05:43,840 --> 00:05:44,600
I know, honey.

100
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:45,400
Okay, okay. It hurts so much.

101
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:46,280
Okay, okay.

102
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:47,960
Hubby, beat him up for me.

103
00:05:48,080 --> 00:05:49,200
- Beat him to death for me.
- Okay, okay.

104
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:50,460
- Hit him for me.
- Okay.

105
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:51,850
Beat him to death for me.

106
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:53,180
They are Japanese.

107
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:55,050
We can't afford to offend them.

108
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:56,400
Can't afford it.

109
00:05:57,080 --> 00:05:58,880
So I'm easy to offend, right?

110
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:00,880
Sister-in-law, I'm easy to offend.

111
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:02,240
I married you when I was 14.

112
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,480
I married you when I was 14. Don't fight.

113
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:04,760
I was still a virgin

114
00:06:04,760 --> 00:06:06,080
when I married you.

115
00:06:06,280 --> 00:06:07,410
I was bullied today.

116
00:06:07,520 --> 00:06:09,120
I was bullied by this short guy.

117
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,840
You won't beat him up, right? I will.

118
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:11,880
I'll go, I'll go. Beat him up.

119
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:12,840
You do it. Hit him.

120
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:14,360
Calm down, calm down.

121
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:16,240
Sir, I'm from the Police Department.

122
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,040
Listen to me.

123
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:18,160
Please bear with us.

124
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:19,200
We work for you.

125
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:20,680
Can you give me some face?

126
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:21,680
Give me some face.

127
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:25,280
What face do you want?

128
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:28,660
She should be severely punished for disturbing the peace.

129
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:30,160
You dare hit my man?

130
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:33,280
See if I don't scratch you to death!

131
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:35,640
You bastard! Bastard!

132
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:39,040
You bastard! You bastard!

133
00:06:39,520 --> 00:06:40,440
Let's go. Let's go.

134
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:42,000
My fault. My fault.

135
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:43,040
My fault.

136
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:44,800
Misunderstanding. Misunderstanding.

137
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:45,400
Get lost!

138
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:46,360
Thank you.

139
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:47,760
Thank you, sir. Thank you, sir.

140
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:50,200
Thank you, sir. Thank you. Thank you.

141
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:52,000
Take care. Take care.

142
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:53,320
Take care.

143
00:06:57,440 --> 00:06:58,400
What are you looking at?

144
00:06:58,400 --> 00:06:59,730
What are you looking at?

145
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:00,320
Get out.

146
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:01,200
Go, go, go.

147
00:07:02,080 --> 00:07:02,880
Get out!

148
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:04,490
What's there to look at?

149
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:06,820
Believe it or not, I'll shoot you.

150
00:07:06,840 --> 00:07:07,560
Brother.

151
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:09,880
Calm down.

152
00:07:14,840 --> 00:07:15,520
Brother.

153
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:17,520
About that prisoner matter,

154
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:18,840
there are only seven days left.

155
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:19,840
What should we do?

156
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:25,520
We still need to find a death row inmate.

157
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:26,920
The favors we need to owe,

158
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,130
we still have to owe.

159
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,440
Did you kill Suzuki Kang?

160
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:01,600
Did you kill Zhu Tianyou?

161
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:06,020
And did you kill those other four people too?

162
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:13,040
Yes.

163
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:16,080
Why didn't you say so earlier?

164
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:33,720
Brother.

165
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:36,480
Our harmonica club is a lot of fun.

166
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:37,960
You can not only learn to play,

167
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:39,690
but also meet many new friends.

168
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:44,560
I...

169
00:08:44,640 --> 00:08:46,400
Can a manual laborer do it?

170
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:48,140
Who says you can't?

171
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:50,200
We have all kinds of people here.

172
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:51,200
Brother.

173
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:53,240
I have an old harmonica here.

174
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:54,440
If you don't mind,

175
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:55,680
I'll give it to you.

176
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:56,200
This...

177
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,560
I can't accept this. It's too precious.

178
00:08:57,560 --> 00:08:58,760
How much do I have to pull?

179
00:08:58,760 --> 00:08:59,560
Keep it.

180
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:01,120
You're welcome anytime.

181
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:14,560
Dongsheng.

182
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:16,560
Mr. Qin.

183
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:18,600
Are you going out?

184
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:20,000
Let me give you a ride.

185
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,320
Okay.

186
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:25,480
Mr. Qin, get on.

187
00:09:25,680 --> 00:09:28,340
You carry a harmonica while pulling a rickshaw?

188
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:31,400
Mr. Gu gave this to me.

189
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:33,440
I practice it when I'm free.

190
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:36,650
What songs can you play?

191
00:09:37,880 --> 00:09:39,800
Currently, I can only play "Battlefield Moon".

192
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:41,260
I'm not very good at it yet.

193
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:42,940
Take your time.

194
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:44,440
You'll master it eventually.

195
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:47,000
The song "Battlefield Moon" is very easy to learn.

196
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,200
Come to the harmonica club when you are free.

197
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,060
I'll teach you.

198
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:58,240
Sit tight, Mr. Qin.

199
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:19,160
The supplies of the 261st Regiment.

200
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:22,520
Indicate a large number of rifles

201
00:10:22,520 --> 00:10:23,440
and grenades.

202
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:26,120
The number on the crates is 101,

203
00:10:26,680 --> 00:10:29,610
which belongs to the Kwantung Army's chemical unit.

204
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:41,760
You, come here.

205
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:43,000
Officer.

206
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:44,920
Nail it shut.

207
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:45,800
Okay.

208
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:47,480
Hurry up.

209
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:12,280
Comrade Dajiang sent a message this morning.

210
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:13,280
This batch of arms

211
00:11:13,560 --> 00:11:14,640
is to support

212
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:18,120
the encirclement of the Jingbo Lake guerrillas next week.

213
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:19,200
Unit 101

214
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:22,210
is responsible for deploying poison gas shells.

215
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:25,740
This intelligence is extremely important.

216
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:30,560
If we know

217
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:32,480
the departure time of this train,

218
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:34,400
we can notify the assault team in advance

219
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:36,280
to blow it up on the way,

220
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:39,600
buying time for delivering the intelligence

221
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:40,560
and relocating the guerrillas.

222
00:11:40,560 --> 00:11:41,820
I heard it's tomorrow,

223
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:43,610
but I don't know the exact time.

224
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:48,640
I'll go to the freight yard dispatch office.

225
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:50,080
The freight yard has sentry posts

226
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:51,040
and searchlights.

227
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:52,100
How will you get in?

228
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:57,680
No, let me think about it.

229
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:01,320
Qin.

230
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:02,840
I'm familiar with that place.

231
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:05,170
It's easy to get into the dispatch office.

232
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:18,010
Is everything okay inside?

233
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:19,440
What could happen?

234
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:24,320
Our job here

235
00:12:25,440 --> 00:12:26,800
is just like a deaf man's ears,

236
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:27,600
just for show.

237
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:28,720
Shut up.

238
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:31,000
Even watermelon can't stop your mouth.

239
00:13:24,880 --> 00:13:25,880
Yes, sir.

240
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:29,410
Everything is normal here.

241
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:31,240
Please rest assured.

242
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:10,600
I forgot my hat.
